title: Number of births in Norway 2008 to 2018
summary: This line chart has an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Number of live births, with a total of 11 data points. The chart has 5 significant trends.
The longest trend is slightly negative which exists from 2018 to 2014.
Contrarily, the next significant trend is extremely negative which exists from 2011 to 2008.
But, the next significant trend is extremely positive which exists from 2014 to 2013.
Likewise, the next significant trend is slightly negative which exists from 2013 to 2012.
Differently, the next significant trend is extremely positive which exists from 2012 to 2011.
